<subSubSection id="C354654FFFD4810969E0FDB6FCCBFCED" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FDB6FE17FD85" blockId="58.[189,399,593,619]" box="[189,399,593,619]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<heading id="D0B981A8FFD4810969E0FDB6FE17FD85" bold="true" box="[189,399,593,619]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD4810969E0FDB6FE17FD85" bold="true" box="[189,399,593,619]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FD67FCCBFCED" blockId="58.[189,1399,639,772]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
† 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096991FD98FEE7FD77" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1915" box="[204,383,639,665]" class="Insecta" genus="Nematophlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD481096991FD98FEE7FD77" box="[204,383,639,665]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Nematophlebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an extinct genus known only from one Early Jurassic species, † 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096D9EFD98FE96FD52" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" genus="Nematophlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plicata">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD481096D9EFD98FE96FD52" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Nematophlebia plicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingRegion id="498AF826FFD481096803FD45FD8EFD52" box="[350,534,674,700]" country="United Kingdom" name="Gloucestershire" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Gloucestershire</collectingRegion>
or 
<collectingRegion id="498AF826FFD481096B60FD45FD7AFD52" box="[573,738,674,700]" country="United Kingdom" name="Warwickshire" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Warwickshire</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3597654FFD481096BB3FD45FCC8FD52" box="[750,848,674,700]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">England</collectingCountry>
(without further locality). The original species description reports only a few general venational characteristics, which are not enough to confidently include this species in any specific megalopteran family.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354654FFFD4810969E0FCCCFD03FC9A" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FCCCFE11FCAA" blockId="58.[189,393,810,837]" box="[189,393,810,837]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<heading id="D0B981A8FFD4810969E0FCCCFE11FCAA" bold="true" box="[189,393,810,837]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD4810969E0FCCCFE11FCAA" bold="true" box="[189,393,810,837]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Included species</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FCBEFD03FC9A" blockId="58.[189,667,857,884]" box="[189,667,857,884]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
† 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096991FCBEFD03FC9A" authority="Cockerell, 1915" authorityName="Cockerell" authorityYear="1915" box="[204,667,857,884]" class="Insecta" genus="Nematophlebia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plicata">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD481096991FCBEFE4FFC9D" box="[204,471,857,883]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">Nematophlebia plicata</emphasis>
Cockerell, 1915
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354654FFFD4810969E0FC6CFD19FC48" box="[189,641,907,934]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FC6CFD19FC48" blockId="58.[189,641,907,934]" box="[189,641,907,934]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Palaearctic (
<collectingCountry id="F3597654FFD481096810FC6CFE2AFC48" box="[333,434,907,934]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">England</collectingCountry>
) [Early Jurassic].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C354654FFFD4810969E0FC29FAFEFAD8" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FC29FD3BFC04" blockId="58.[189,675,973,1003]" box="[189,675,973,1003]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B93AEAD6FFD4810969E0FC29FD3BFC04" bold="true" box="[189,675,973,1003]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
Taxa excluded from the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD4810968A1FC2AFD3BFC04" authorityName="Martins &amp; Ardila-Camacho &amp; Rivera-Gasperín &amp; Oswald &amp; Liu &amp; Contreras-Ramos" authorityYear="2022" box="[508,675,973,1002]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Megaloptera</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF136C4FFD4810969E0FBE4FAFEFAD8" blockId="58.[188,1400,1026,1334]" pageId="58" pageNumber="59">
In addition to the species above, which we recognize here as belonging to the order 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096DDFFBE5FA81FBF2" authorityName="Martins &amp; Ardila-Camacho &amp; Rivera-Gasperín &amp; Oswald &amp; Liu &amp; Contreras-Ramos" authorityYear="2022" box="[1154,1305,1026,1052]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Megaloptera</taxonomicName>
, several other taxa have been placed in the order by some authors. We list below the taxa that are known to us that have previously been included in the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096BF1FBAEFCD8FB8D" authorityName="Martins &amp; Ardila-Camacho &amp; Rivera-Gasperín &amp; Oswald &amp; Liu &amp; Contreras-Ramos" authorityYear="2022" box="[684,832,1097,1123]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Megaloptera</taxonomicName>
by one or more previous authors, but which are now excluded. For each taxon we provide brief taxonomic notes about its current placement. In the synonymical listings in this section we make no attempt to be comprehensive. We present only enough synonymy to document original taxon placements, prominent intermediate placements (in some cases), and current placements (outside 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD481096B65FB32FD4AFB1E" authorityName="Martins &amp; Ardila-Camacho &amp; Rivera-Gasperín &amp; Oswald &amp; Liu &amp; Contreras-Ramos" authorityYear="2022" box="[568,722,1237,1264]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Megaloptera</taxonomicName>
). Because our primary intent is to document the exclusion of certain taxa from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4E4D47FFD4810968E4FB1EFDC8FAFD" authorityName="Martins &amp; Ardila-Camacho &amp; Rivera-Gasperín &amp; Oswald &amp; Liu &amp; Contreras-Ramos" authorityYear="2022" box="[441,592,1273,1299]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="58" pageNumber="59" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Megaloptera</taxonomicName>
, we make no attempt to provide comprehensive sub-taxon listings (e.g., of genera within families, or species within genera) of the higher taxa included in the list below.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
